This sfx-translator.js implementation provides:
Core Translation Modes:
Direct: Keep romaji (ドキドキ → dokidoki) - for hardcore fans
Adaptive: Cultural localization (ドキドキ → thump thump / ba-dump ba-dump)
Visual: Descriptive meaning (ドキドキ → [heartbeat])
Hybrid: Combined approach (BA-DUMP dokidoki)
Genre-Authentic: Context-aware (shonen gets bold impacts, shoujo gets soft emotions)
Comprehensive SFX Database:
Physical: ドン (impact), バン (bang), ガタガタ (rattle)
Atmospheric: ゴゴゴ (ominous rumble), ザワザワ (unease), ポカポカ (warmth)
Physiological: ドキドキ (heartbeat), ブルブル (shiver), ゴク (gulp)
Emotional: イライラ (irritation), ムカムカ (nausea/anger), ガーン (shock)
Visual States: ピカピカ (sparkle), メラメラ (blaze), キラキラ (glitter)
Actions: ペコペコ (bowing), バタバタ (panic), ジロジロ (staring)
Advanced Features:
Visual Metadata Generation: Font styles, colors, effects matching original intensity
Genre Detection: Shonen/shoujo/horror/comedy/slice-of-life context awareness
Intensity Preservation: Maps 1-5 intensity scale to typography weight
Batch Consistency: Ensures same SFX translated identically across a scene
Romaji Fallback: Transliteration engine for unknown sound effects
Cultural Adaptation:
English: BAM, thump thump, sparkle, CRACKLE
Spanish: PUM, latido, brillo, crepitar
French: BOUM, battement, brillant, crépitement
Visual Integration:
Typography matching (Impact for heavy hits, Comic Sans for soft sounds)
Color coding (red for impact, pink for physiological, orange for emotion)
Shape suggestions (burst for impacts, cloud for atmosphere, spiky for action)
Animation hints (pulse for intense SFX, sparkle for キラキラ)
Manga-Specific Logic:
JoJo Style: Special handling for ゴゴゴ (menacing) with vibration effects
Shoujo Romance: Soft gradients for ドキドキ, star effects for キラキラ
Battle Manga: Bold uppercase for impacts, motion line suggestions
Horror: Distorted fonts for ザワザワ (unease), dark colors
Integration Points:
Works with ConfigManager for user preferences
Uses ImageUtils for bounding box calculations
Provides data for overlay-injector.js visual rendering
Supports context-preserver.js for scene consistency
The system ensures that sound effects maintain their narrative impact while becoming accessible to international readers, with intelligent defaults that respect both the original artistic intent and target audience expectations.